result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Juan Moralez Jr in court.  Attorney Haley E Wentz in court for Juan Moralez Jr.  Prosecuting attorney Nate Kristian McClure in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Parties are prepared to enter into a deferred prosecution agreement.
AS TO COUNT 1:
Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Complaint/Information.  Court WITHHELD entry of judgment of conviction.  Deferred Prosecution Agreement received, signed and filed.
 
Court ordered case adjourned for Review in Branch 17.
Review hearing scheduled for November 14, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Juan Moralez in court with attorney Haley E Wentz.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Juan Moralez appeared by video means with Attorney.
Case heard off the record due to court reporter availability.
Defense counsel informed the Court that this case is in DPA posture and defendant has TAD evaluation scheduled 07/28/2022.
Court ordered case adjourned for DPA hearing in Branch 37. All parties are advised effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to a Branch of RESERVE JUDGES.
Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for 09/13/2022 at 08:30 a.m.

Defendant Juan Moralez in court with attorney Haley E Wentz.  Nate Kristian McClure appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Juan Moralez appeared by video means with Attorney.   Defense counsel has received discovery and has not received an offer and requests additional time to review.   Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 37.  Status conference scheduled for July 22, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Juan Moralez in court.  Matthew Richard Westphal appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant IS Public Defender eligible. Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  
The case is adjourned to Br. 37 for a Pretrial Conference.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 9, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 05/16/2022@1:30pm
